<!-- ── WHAT TO EXPECT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>What to Expect on Sunday</h2>
      <p>We want your first visit to feel comfortable and familiar, not overwhelming.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-2-col">

      <div class="expect-step">
        <div class="expect-number">1</div>
        <div>
          <h3>You'll Be Greeted Warmly</h3>
          <p>
            From the moment you arrive, you'll be welcomed by friendly faces.
            Our greeters are happy to answer questions, help you find a seat,
            or point you toward the restrooms. No one will put you on the spot,
            we promise.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="expect-step">
        <div class="expect-number">2</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Worship Together as a Family</h3>
          <p>
            The service opens with worship, a blend of beloved traditional
            hymns and contemporary worship songs. Families sit together during
            this time, so children and teens are with you from the start.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="expect-step">
        <div class="expect-number">3</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Kids &amp; Teens Are Dismissed to Their Classes</h3>
          <p>
            After worship, kids (ages 3–11) go to Children's Worship and
            teens (ages 12–19) head to Youth Group. On the 3rd Sunday of the
            month, children stay with their adults the entire service for
            Family Worship. Youth Group meets every week.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="expect-step">
        <div class="expect-number">4</div>
        <div>
          <h3>The Message</h3>
          <p>
            Pastor Dan preaches from Scripture in a way that is accessible,
            practical, and grounded in the Bible. We believe God's Word has
            something relevant and life-giving to say to each of us, wherever
            we are in our journey.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── WORSHIP STYLE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="bg-light">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="welcome-grid">
      <div class="welcome-text">
        <h2>Our Worship Style</h2>
        <p>
          At SWBC, worship draws from the best of two traditions. You'll
          hear classic hymns that have anchored the church for generations
          alongside contemporary praise songs that feel fresh and vibrant.
        </p>
        <p>
          Whether you grew up singing out of a hymnal or you're more
          comfortable with a modern worship experience, you'll find something
          that resonates. Our goal is simply to lead our congregation into the
          presence of God, joyfully and authentically.
        </p>
        <p>
          Song lyrics are displayed on screen so you can follow along
          easily, even if you're unfamiliar with a particular song.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="scripture-card">
        <blockquote>
          "Sing to the Lord a new song; sing to the Lord, all the earth.
          Sing to the Lord, praise his name; proclaim his salvation
          day after day."
        </blockquote>
        <cite>Psalm 96:1–2 (NIV)</cite>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

